      drainage of tears from eyes to nose. An attempt will be made to open the passage whereby a fine metal probe will be inserted so as to
      overcome the blockage. The procedure will be done under General Anaesthesia.
      <li> Syringing and Probing is successful in 95% of cases of nasolacrimal duct blockage that are caused by a simple duct blockage.</li>
      <li> The procedure needs to be repeated sometimes if the blockage is not relieved.</li>
      <li> The tear duct may have a complicated type of obstruction or the tear duct might not have developed completely. These complications
      may be noticed at the time of surgery during probing. Further surgery may be required consequently.</li>
      <li> Bleeding from the nose can occur for upto three days after surgery.</li>
      <li> Lid swelling can occur due to false passage and extravasation of saline.</li>
